1
00:02:11,879 --> 00:02:13,240
I'm glad

2
00:02:13,879 --> 00:02:17,439
all four of us are finally together.

3
00:02:41,759 --> 00:02:43,560
Daddy, I want to see Lin Bing the panda.

4
00:02:44,879 --> 00:02:45,719
Of course, son.

5
00:02:46,199 --> 00:02:47,360
We will go today.

6
00:02:47,840 --> 00:02:48,800
We will all go together.

7
00:02:48,879 --> 00:02:49,919
I would rather sleep.

8
00:02:51,520 --> 00:02:53,639
Please, can we go?

9
00:02:54,599 --> 00:02:56,520
Please, Nan.

10
00:02:56,759 --> 00:02:58,879
Please.

11
00:03:16,960 --> 00:03:19,800
LADDALAND

12
00:04:39,560 --> 00:04:41,199
-You like it?
-Yes.

13
00:04:52,040 --> 00:04:54,160
Mom, I want to take a look inside.

14
00:04:54,240 --> 00:04:56,279
Wait, let's take a picture first.

15
00:04:59,279 --> 00:05:00,959
Take a picture later.
Pay off the house first.

16
00:05:30,040 --> 00:05:31,000
Do you like it?

17
00:05:31,600 --> 00:05:32,639
Dad did this himself.

18
00:05:45,000 --> 00:05:47,160
How nice, you can see the mountain
from your window.

19
00:05:47,480 --> 00:05:49,160
You don't have a view like this
in Bangkok.

20
00:05:49,279 --> 00:05:51,319
Mom, do you know what Bangkok has?

21
00:05:52,040 --> 00:05:55,160
Grandma, my school, and my friends.

22
00:05:57,079 --> 00:05:58,920
You aren't the only one
who left everything behind.

23
00:05:59,000 --> 00:06:01,600
I told you that I don't want to be here,
yet you still dragged me here.

24
00:06:02,000 --> 00:06:04,000
Why, did you love me all of the sudden?

25
00:06:04,319 --> 00:06:06,399
There was only Nat back then.
You guys were fine.

26
00:06:11,160 --> 00:06:12,839
NAT

27
00:06:19,160 --> 00:06:20,879
Ben 10!

28
00:06:21,560 --> 00:06:25,680
Ben 10!

29
00:06:25,800 --> 00:06:28,079
Wow, Gekiranger.

30
00:06:37,120 --> 00:06:39,920
Dad, what is that?
Why is it following you?

31
00:06:40,759 --> 00:06:41,800
Yes.

32
00:06:41,920 --> 00:06:44,560
It follows us everywhere
no matter where we walk.

33
00:06:44,639 --> 00:06:46,079
Do you know what it is?

34
00:06:46,879 --> 00:06:48,000
It's a...

35
00:06:49,120 --> 00:06:51,120
magic eye.

36
00:06:53,759 --> 00:06:54,680
Moron.

37
00:06:55,720 --> 00:06:57,120
It's called an eye sensor.

38
00:06:57,800 --> 00:06:59,480
All the new air-conditioners
have this feature.

39
00:06:59,560 --> 00:07:00,879
It's called a "magic eye."

40
00:07:01,399 --> 00:07:03,600
How else does it know where we are?

41
00:07:04,240 --> 00:07:05,920
If you want to be an idiot, be my guest.

42
00:07:08,120 --> 00:07:10,639
Cut it out.
No fighting at the dinner table.

43
00:07:18,800 --> 00:07:23,759
I'm glad all four of us are finally...

44
00:07:27,040 --> 00:07:28,279
Hi, Grandma.

45
00:07:29,040 --> 00:07:31,959
Oh, I was busy unpacking.

46
00:07:35,079 --> 00:07:36,600
It's okay.

47
00:07:37,360 --> 00:07:38,959
It's a housing project.

48
00:07:39,160 --> 00:07:40,879
If it was run down,
it won't be able to sell.

49
00:07:43,720 --> 00:07:46,959
My own TV?

50
00:07:47,519 --> 00:07:49,560
We're already lucky
to have one for the whole house.

51
00:07:50,439 --> 00:07:51,360
Nan,

52
00:07:51,680 --> 00:07:53,079
don't take a phone call during dinner.

53
00:07:53,160 --> 00:07:54,000
Yes,

54
00:07:54,079 --> 00:07:56,680
my teacher taught me
not to take a phone call during dinner.

55
00:07:56,920 --> 00:07:58,079
It's bad manners.

56
00:07:58,399 --> 00:08:01,800
And has your teacher ever taught you
not to interrupt during a conversation?

57
00:08:03,560 --> 00:08:05,319
Nan, speak nicely to your brother.

58
00:08:45,600 --> 00:08:47,840
What's so funny?
I tried really hard to surprise you.

59
00:08:47,919 --> 00:08:49,320
Okay. Sorry.

60
00:08:49,519 --> 00:08:51,120
I'll open it then.

61
00:08:54,320 --> 00:08:55,759
Put the glasses down first, maybe?

62
00:08:56,600 --> 00:08:57,840
Yes, I forgot.

63
00:08:59,279 --> 00:09:00,360
Do you need my help?

64
00:09:00,720 --> 00:09:02,039
No, just stand over there.

65
00:09:07,080 --> 00:09:09,000
Show off.

66
00:09:10,080 --> 00:09:11,759
-Damn it!
-Oh, my god!

67
00:09:12,919 --> 00:09:14,679
Thee, get the water!

68
00:09:14,879 --> 00:09:15,759
Shit!

69
00:09:15,840 --> 00:09:16,679
Hold on.

70
00:09:20,039 --> 00:09:21,080
Hurry up, Thee.

71
00:09:27,919 --> 00:09:30,279
Instead of christening the house,

72
00:09:30,600 --> 00:09:33,559
you celebrate with a bottle of wine
and almost burned the house down.

73
00:09:34,679 --> 00:09:38,159
It will be fine.
Just get the maid to clean up.

74
00:09:38,600 --> 00:09:40,480
When you went to pick up the kids,

75
00:09:40,759 --> 00:09:42,120
I hired a Burmese maid.

76
00:09:42,559 --> 00:09:44,000
She does a fine job.

77
00:09:46,480 --> 00:09:48,360
Let's save as much as we can, Thee.

78
00:09:48,759 --> 00:09:50,240
You earn 60,000 baht a month.

79
00:09:50,720 --> 00:09:52,440
The mortgage alone is 30,000 baht.

80
00:09:53,399 --> 00:09:54,759
Parn, don't worry.

81
00:09:54,840 --> 00:09:58,639
Don't forget that I take commissions too.

82
00:10:00,519 --> 00:10:03,279
Yoi told me I can expect at least
another 20,000 baht a month.

83
00:10:04,200 --> 00:10:05,639
Or else I wouldn't dare to live here.

84
00:10:06,200 --> 00:10:09,360
Everyone who has joined our business

85
00:10:09,919 --> 00:10:12,799
could say that they are financially set
for the rest of their lives.

86
00:10:12,960 --> 00:10:14,200
EMPIRE
DIETARY SUPPLEMENT

87
00:10:18,000 --> 00:10:20,519
My assistant, Mr. Theera,
is a great example.

88
00:10:21,519 --> 00:10:25,679
He used to work at
an air condition company in Bangkok.

89
00:10:25,919 --> 00:10:29,360
He has a dream like you all.
To own a house one day.

90
00:10:30,039 --> 00:10:32,120
He had worked for 14 years.

91
00:10:32,639 --> 00:10:33,919
Fourteen years!

92
00:10:34,039 --> 00:10:38,000
In the end, that company couldn't make
his dream come true.

93
00:10:41,879 --> 00:10:45,200
But within only three months

94
00:10:45,279 --> 00:10:48,559
since Mr. Theera has joined us.

95
00:10:49,000 --> 00:10:52,320
Would you like to know
what he got last month?

96
00:10:52,679 --> 00:10:55,480
Mr. Theera, why don't you tell everyone
what you got last month?

97
00:10:57,440 --> 00:10:59,559
I put the down payment on a house.

98
00:10:59,639 --> 00:11:01,480
A down payment! Wow!

99
00:11:01,559 --> 00:11:03,080
Let's give him a round of applause!

100
00:11:05,039 --> 00:11:06,000
Excellent.

101
00:11:35,080 --> 00:11:35,919
Mom?

102
00:11:36,000 --> 00:11:38,039
How come Nan has to
take the bus to school?

103
00:11:38,360 --> 00:11:41,240
I gave you the car
to take my children home.

104
00:11:41,360 --> 00:11:42,679
It's not for your husband!

105
00:11:43,200 --> 00:11:45,120
I helped raise Nan for over ten years.

106
00:11:45,399 --> 00:11:47,320
I have never put her
in an unsafe situation.

107
00:11:47,960 --> 00:11:51,159
Mom, your grandchild is also my daughter.

108
00:11:51,320 --> 00:11:53,440
And Nan is already 14.

109
00:11:53,559 --> 00:11:55,480
There are kids younger than Nan
who take the bus.

110
00:11:55,639 --> 00:11:57,840
Stop making excuses for your husband.

111
00:11:58,320 --> 00:11:59,679
I'm not making any excuses.

112
00:11:59,919 --> 00:12:01,559
But you got to be fair to him, too.

113
00:12:02,039 --> 00:12:04,240
You never congratulate him
when he bought the house.

114
00:12:04,600 --> 00:12:07,200
And now I don't have to work anymore.

115
00:12:07,519 --> 00:12:09,480
Why should I give him credit

116
00:12:09,559 --> 00:12:11,440
for doing what he is supposed to do?

117
00:12:16,720 --> 00:12:18,720
Mom, I got to go now.
I need to go buy some groceries.

118
00:12:19,759 --> 00:12:22,679
Go ahead. You got to catch a bus.

119
00:12:23,320 --> 00:12:24,840
Hurry up before it gets
any hotter outside.

120
00:12:25,559 --> 00:12:26,600
Okay.

121
00:12:49,559 --> 00:12:51,279
Hey. Go away.

122
00:12:52,240 --> 00:12:53,120
Go!

123
00:12:54,200 --> 00:12:55,080
Go!

124
00:13:31,720 --> 00:13:34,200
You always say that my mom
likes to spoil her kids, so what's this?

125
00:13:36,279 --> 00:13:38,399
There's a zero percent interest promotion.

126
00:13:38,960 --> 00:13:40,639
Don't worry. I can make the payments.

127
00:13:41,240 --> 00:13:42,679
Nat will want one, too.

128
00:13:46,320 --> 00:13:47,879
Whose cat pooped here?

129
00:13:53,600 --> 00:13:54,679
Here you are.

130
00:13:54,879 --> 00:13:55,759
Thee!

131
00:13:56,759 --> 00:13:57,679
What the heck?

132
00:14:02,919 --> 00:14:03,759
Do you have a problem?

133
00:14:05,240 --> 00:14:06,320
I am sorry.

134
00:14:07,120 --> 00:14:09,399
I was trying to hit the cat
that pooped in my yard.

135
00:14:10,200 --> 00:14:11,639
My cat did that?

136
00:14:11,799 --> 00:14:12,720
-Yes.
-Then I'm sorry.

137
00:14:12,799 --> 00:14:13,759
I will take care of it.

138
00:14:14,120 --> 00:14:14,960
Okay.

139
00:14:15,120 --> 00:14:15,960
Nid.

140
00:14:16,440 --> 00:14:18,840
-Nid.
-That's okay. It's not a big deal.

141
00:14:19,360 --> 00:14:20,240
Don't worry.

142
00:14:20,519 --> 00:14:21,440
I'm Somkiat.

143
00:14:22,120 --> 00:14:25,080
I went to work in Bangkok for a month

144
00:14:25,480 --> 00:14:26,600
so I didn't get to say hello.

145
00:14:26,799 --> 00:14:29,039
I am Thee and this is Parn, my wife.

146
00:14:29,320 --> 00:14:30,399
-Hello.
-Hello.

147
00:14:32,200 --> 00:14:34,159
Chowguay took a dump in their yard.

148
00:14:34,399 --> 00:14:35,679
Get a broom and clean it for them.

149
00:14:36,960 --> 00:14:37,840
I am so sorry.

150
00:14:37,919 --> 00:14:39,279
I will take care of it.

151
00:14:39,519 --> 00:14:41,639
Oh, don't worry. I'll take care of it.

152
00:14:43,279 --> 00:14:44,720
Oh, no. I better do it.

153
00:14:45,519 --> 00:14:47,480
Take this and clean it for them too.

154
00:14:53,519 --> 00:14:54,919
Excuse me, I got to go now.

155
00:15:01,879 --> 00:15:03,879
I think Somkiat's family is a bit strange.

156
00:15:03,960 --> 00:15:05,759
Just let them be.

157
00:15:45,039 --> 00:15:45,879
Hey!

158
00:15:46,480 --> 00:15:47,320
Hey!

159
00:15:47,480 --> 00:15:49,639
About my offer to work at my house...

160
00:15:55,000 --> 00:15:56,440
Hey, you.

161
00:15:57,360 --> 00:15:58,240
Hey.

162
00:16:20,399 --> 00:16:24,440
-I'm serious, Mom. Taew has a crush on me.
-Why do you think so?

163
00:16:24,639 --> 00:16:26,080
Because I am handsome.

164
00:16:26,759 --> 00:16:30,120
Yes, you are the most handsome boy
in the world.

165
00:16:34,399 --> 00:16:36,879
Mom, a police car. Hurry!

166
00:16:37,000 --> 00:16:38,759
Nat, don't run.

167
00:16:41,960 --> 00:16:43,360
Nobody lives here.

168
00:16:43,440 --> 00:16:47,240
The foreigner owns the house
but he barely comes to stay.

169
00:16:47,320 --> 00:16:49,159
He usually comes around the New Year.

170
00:16:49,320 --> 00:16:52,159
When was the last time you saw the maid?

171
00:16:52,679 --> 00:16:54,000
Several days ago.

172
00:16:54,080 --> 00:16:56,320
I noticed that the door
was broken this morning.

173
00:16:56,559 --> 00:16:58,480
So I called the police right away.

174
00:16:58,639 --> 00:17:00,200
Mom, lift me up.

175
00:17:04,160 --> 00:17:05,799
Mom, what are they doing?

176
00:17:06,839 --> 00:17:10,039
Maybe they are filming a movie.

177
00:17:11,759 --> 00:17:13,599
Lieutenant, the back door was pried open.

178
00:17:13,680 --> 00:17:15,160
I will go inside to check.

179
00:17:15,359 --> 00:17:16,920
Affirmative. Be careful.

180
00:17:17,240 --> 00:17:22,079
Lieutenant, the house
has been ransacked...

181
00:17:24,839 --> 00:17:27,079
and stinks.

182
00:17:32,119 --> 00:17:33,319
Oh, shit!

183
00:17:37,240 --> 00:17:38,960
What happened, sergeant?

184
00:17:39,039 --> 00:17:41,480
There is a female body
stuffed inside the fridge.

185
00:17:41,559 --> 00:17:44,039
Her face is completely disfigured.

186
00:17:50,200 --> 00:17:53,599
There was a homicide at house no.8

187
00:17:53,680 --> 00:17:57,640
in Laddaland Village, Muang district,
Chiang Mai province.

188
00:17:57,720 --> 00:18:01,799
The police have found
the body of a Burmese woman

189
00:18:01,960 --> 00:18:04,720
who is believed to be about 20 years old.

190
00:18:04,799 --> 00:18:08,079
The body was beaten
with a thick wooden stick

191
00:18:08,160 --> 00:18:11,359
and her face was severely burned by acid.

192
00:18:11,440 --> 00:18:13,440
The murderer tried to hide

193
00:18:13,519 --> 00:18:16,119
her body inside the refrigerator.

194
00:18:16,200 --> 00:18:17,880
The police suspects that

195
00:18:17,960 --> 00:18:20,160
the murderer must have known the victim.

196
00:18:20,240 --> 00:18:23,559
The motive for this homicide
is an extramarital affair.

197
00:18:24,119 --> 00:18:25,160
Thee.

198
00:18:26,079 --> 00:18:27,839
Someone died in our village today.

199
00:18:29,440 --> 00:18:32,559
It was the Burmese maid
at the foreigner's house on the corner.

200
00:18:36,079 --> 00:18:37,240
How is that possible?

201
00:18:38,000 --> 00:18:38,880
Why?

202
00:18:42,440 --> 00:18:43,279
Nothing.

203
00:18:44,039 --> 00:18:45,200
Has Nan heard about this?

204
00:18:50,799 --> 00:18:51,920
Not yet.

205
00:18:52,119 --> 00:18:54,200
Good, don't tell her yet.

206
00:18:54,839 --> 00:18:56,480
Or else your mom will call
and complain again.

207
00:19:10,519 --> 00:19:14,079
It's bad that this had to happen
in our village.

208
00:19:18,680 --> 00:19:22,759
There are dead people in every village.
We just didn't know about it.

209
00:21:21,240 --> 00:21:22,240
Shit!

210
00:21:37,559 --> 00:21:40,000
LADDALAND

211
00:21:53,359 --> 00:21:54,720
EMPIRE DIETARY SUPPLEMENT

212
00:21:55,519 --> 00:21:57,440
CHIANG MAI MAP

213
00:21:57,519 --> 00:22:01,559
MR. NATTACHAI
MR. NITIWAT

214
00:22:17,279 --> 00:22:19,079
Parn, take her to bed.

215
00:22:19,920 --> 00:22:20,880
Let's go honey.

216
00:22:27,319 --> 00:22:29,519
Let me go!

217
00:22:29,599 --> 00:22:32,279
-Let me go!
-Please calm down.

218
00:22:34,960 --> 00:22:39,119
Makin! Let me go!

219
00:22:39,200 --> 00:22:43,799
Makin! Let me go!

220
00:22:43,880 --> 00:22:48,480
She is here! Let me go!

221
00:22:48,720 --> 00:22:51,880
Let me go!

222
00:23:36,400 --> 00:23:37,880
Someone died in our village,

223
00:23:38,200 --> 00:23:39,519
and you didn't think of telling me?

224
00:24:00,519 --> 00:24:03,200
It got to the point that
Chat's husband is selling the house.

225
00:24:03,519 --> 00:24:06,640
They saw Makin walking around their house.

226
00:24:06,720 --> 00:24:08,559
Nobody would want to stay.

227
00:24:08,640 --> 00:24:11,880
I wouldn't even come back to pack
if I were them.

228
00:24:11,960 --> 00:24:16,279
Please pray for her soul.

229
00:24:16,480 --> 00:24:19,440
I almost hired her to work at my house.

230
00:24:19,759 --> 00:24:21,480
I'm lucky that I didn't.

231
00:24:21,599 --> 00:24:24,039
Else, I'd be freaking out now.

232
00:25:33,279 --> 00:25:36,519
Thee, do you remember the girl
that you wanted to hire?

233
00:25:39,400 --> 00:25:40,960
That girl left a long time ago.

234
00:25:42,119 --> 00:25:44,279
Stop listening to
all that nonsense already.

235
00:25:51,799 --> 00:25:53,119
Are the kids asleep?

236
00:25:54,759 --> 00:25:57,799
Nat is. But Nan is not home yet.

237
00:25:58,960 --> 00:26:01,319
She went to her friend's house
to work on a report.

238
00:26:01,400 --> 00:26:03,799
We just moved
and she is already coming home late?

239
00:26:06,440 --> 00:26:08,079
You should lecture her.

240
00:26:35,319 --> 00:26:36,279
What happened?

241
00:26:36,359 --> 00:26:38,599
A girl came out of nowhere
and ran in front of my car.

242
00:26:38,680 --> 00:26:39,839
I almost hit her.

243
00:26:40,200 --> 00:26:41,519
So close.

244
00:27:21,319 --> 00:27:22,240
Ma'am.

245
00:27:26,839 --> 00:27:28,559
Are you okay?

246
00:27:48,400 --> 00:27:49,240
Shit!

247
00:27:50,640 --> 00:27:52,200
Do you want to come live with me?

248
00:27:53,200 --> 00:27:55,559
LADDALAND

249
00:27:59,039 --> 00:28:00,200
Thee, let's go to bed.

250
00:28:00,960 --> 00:28:03,720
Nan called that she's almost done.
Her friend will drop her off.

251
00:28:06,319 --> 00:28:07,880
I will go downstairs to finish up my work.

252
00:28:28,880 --> 00:28:29,720
Nan.

253
00:28:33,480 --> 00:28:34,359
Nan.

254
00:28:46,680 --> 00:28:47,519
Nan.

255
00:28:51,039 --> 00:28:51,920
Nan.

256
00:30:50,279 --> 00:30:51,279
Your move, punk.

257
00:31:00,720 --> 00:31:01,599
Thee!

258
00:31:02,440 --> 00:31:03,720
I don't think he took anything.

259
00:31:04,720 --> 00:31:05,880
I came downstairs just in time.

260
00:31:08,240 --> 00:31:09,279
Yes, correct.

261
00:31:13,559 --> 00:31:14,440
Yes.

262
00:31:15,599 --> 00:31:16,759
Yes. Laddaland Village.

263
00:31:17,119 --> 00:31:17,960
Thank you.

264
00:31:37,960 --> 00:31:38,920
What happened to you?

265
00:31:39,119 --> 00:31:40,160
Who dropped you off?

266
00:31:42,240 --> 00:31:44,160
-My friend.
-A girl or a guy?

267
00:31:45,079 --> 00:31:46,039
It's just a friend.

268
00:31:46,200 --> 00:31:47,920
What's the difference
if it was a girl or a guy?

269
00:31:48,119 --> 00:31:50,000
-How come you're home so late?
-I already told Mom.

270
00:31:50,079 --> 00:31:50,960
I know that!

271
00:31:51,680 --> 00:31:53,400
But what kind of report
took you until 1 a.m.?

272
00:31:54,559 --> 00:31:55,960
The kind that wasn't finished!

273
00:31:56,440 --> 00:31:57,799
I would have come home if it was done.

274
00:31:58,519 --> 00:31:59,799
Don't you think I wasn't sleepy too?

275
00:32:00,119 --> 00:32:01,480
I have to get up for school tomorrow.

276
00:32:01,839 --> 00:32:03,880
-Nan!
-I will go talk to her.

277
00:32:13,599 --> 00:32:14,480
Hey!

278
00:32:14,640 --> 00:32:16,480
Don't point the gun at anyone like that.

279
00:32:17,960 --> 00:32:19,559
It's not loaded.

280
00:32:19,720 --> 00:32:22,480
It's a gun. It's always dangerous.

281
00:32:23,119 --> 00:32:24,960
You better be careful
if you want to use it.

282
00:32:25,079 --> 00:32:28,759
I just wanted it for protection.

283
00:32:29,079 --> 00:32:30,519
A burglar just broke into my house.

284
00:32:50,880 --> 00:32:53,240
Always spending.
Ever think of earning money?

285
00:32:53,319 --> 00:32:55,960
I've tried to find more customers.

286
00:32:56,279 --> 00:33:00,440
You mean your sewing business?
That doesn't earn crap.

287
00:33:01,000 --> 00:33:03,920
All the food you eat.
It comes from money I earn!

288
00:33:04,000 --> 00:33:07,119
Why don't you stop buying
our kid expensive toys then?

289
00:33:09,599 --> 00:33:11,359
Don't you dare lecture me!

290
00:34:00,720 --> 00:34:02,440
Chowguay, wait!

291
00:34:03,319 --> 00:34:04,759
Chowguay, stop!

292
00:34:05,039 --> 00:34:05,920
Stop!

293
00:34:06,839 --> 00:34:09,400
It's good for them to play together.

294
00:34:09,960 --> 00:34:11,239
We don't have to tire ourselves out.

295
00:34:17,199 --> 00:34:18,679
How is your mother-in-law?

296
00:34:21,599 --> 00:34:23,840
She has the same disease.

297
00:34:24,480 --> 00:34:28,559
But now it's getting worse.

298
00:34:29,480 --> 00:34:33,000
The doctor recommended
a complete checkup in Bangkok.

299
00:34:37,079 --> 00:34:40,079
You're not scared
that it's just the two of you?

300
00:34:44,559 --> 00:34:46,159
What can I do?

301
00:34:46,880 --> 00:34:51,559
How about this? When Mr. Somkiat
isn't home and you are free,

302
00:34:51,760 --> 00:34:53,199
you can hang out at my house.

303
00:34:56,159 --> 00:34:59,440
Dad, Chowguay is a spy.

304
00:35:00,960 --> 00:35:02,719
His collar has a camera.

305
00:35:03,000 --> 00:35:04,679
My dad said it is very popular in Bangkok.

306
00:35:04,840 --> 00:35:06,840
-Dad, let take a look at the photos.
-Okay.

307
00:35:08,239 --> 00:35:09,159
Hurry, Dad.

308
00:35:11,239 --> 00:35:13,559
My notebook is upstairs. This way.

309
00:35:14,920 --> 00:35:17,199
Nat, don't run upstairs. You might slip.

310
00:35:18,400 --> 00:35:23,119
Parn, can I ask you something?

311
00:35:27,119 --> 00:35:29,639
Shall we see where the cat went?

312
00:35:30,920 --> 00:35:31,840
Here, Dad.

313
00:35:31,920 --> 00:35:33,519
That's a pool.

314
00:35:34,079 --> 00:35:37,280
-That's Aunt Dang
-It's the pool at our village.

315
00:35:37,960 --> 00:35:40,480
-I can see just the legs
-It spied on us too.

316
00:35:41,400 --> 00:35:43,519
Hey, those are my legs and Golf's.

317
00:35:49,400 --> 00:35:50,880
Look at this photo.

318
00:36:05,119 --> 00:36:06,199
What's the matter, Parn?

319
00:36:36,320 --> 00:36:37,679
Pip, why did you stop?

320
00:36:37,920 --> 00:36:39,239
Because Pai did.

321
00:36:42,239 --> 00:36:44,719
Hey, what are you doing?
Just take me home.

322
00:36:48,159 --> 00:36:50,239
Is this the house where that person died?

323
00:36:50,599 --> 00:36:53,599
Don't you see the yellow tape?

324
00:36:53,679 --> 00:36:56,199
It looks just like in the movies.
Let's check it out.

325
00:36:56,400 --> 00:36:58,440
Are you nuts?
Why the heck do you want to go inside?

326
00:36:58,599 --> 00:37:01,599
Let's check it out.
It will be quite a thrill...

327
00:37:02,840 --> 00:37:06,440
I don't want to get home late.
My dad already yelled at me last time.

328
00:37:06,519 --> 00:37:08,239
Are you that afraid of your dad?

329
00:37:14,159 --> 00:37:17,800
You guys go in. I'm wearing a skirt.
I don't want to climb the fence.

330
00:37:19,000 --> 00:37:21,039
She doesn't want to climb up
because she's wearing a skirt.

331
00:37:21,800 --> 00:37:22,639
Up to you.

332
00:37:25,440 --> 00:37:27,760
-Okay.
-Fine.

333
00:37:29,320 --> 00:37:30,400
Wait.

334
00:37:37,079 --> 00:37:40,480
-I'm feeling cold with no reasons.
-Let me take some photos.

335
00:37:51,360 --> 00:37:52,280
Hey, what's that?

336
00:37:59,000 --> 00:37:59,880
Stop.

337
00:38:00,079 --> 00:38:02,519
I'm just messing with you.

338
00:38:02,679 --> 00:38:04,360
Damn you.

339
00:38:04,559 --> 00:38:05,480
Come on.

340
00:38:21,239 --> 00:38:22,800
You're bad.

341
00:38:23,639 --> 00:38:24,559
Pip.

342
00:38:25,320 --> 00:38:26,400
Pip.

343
00:38:27,480 --> 00:38:30,000
-Don't go inside.
-We will go in just a few minutes.

344
00:39:16,440 --> 00:39:19,039
PIP

345
00:39:22,320 --> 00:39:24,679
Sorry. This number...

346
00:40:08,960 --> 00:40:09,800
Pip.

347
00:40:37,639 --> 00:40:38,480
Pip.

348
00:40:42,320 --> 00:40:43,199
Pip!

349
00:41:29,119 --> 00:41:31,840
-Stop messing around. It's not funny!
-Got you there!

350
00:41:31,920 --> 00:41:34,360
What are you doing here?
I thought you said you aren't coming in.

351
00:41:34,480 --> 00:41:35,639
That was fun!

352
00:41:47,480 --> 00:41:50,000
Hey! what are you doing? Open it!

353
00:41:50,360 --> 00:41:51,360
Open it!

354
00:42:00,519 --> 00:42:01,440
Mai.

355
00:42:03,920 --> 00:42:04,880
Pip.

356
00:43:15,480 --> 00:43:16,480
Nan.

357
00:43:16,679 --> 00:43:17,920
Nan, wait!

358
00:43:18,039 --> 00:43:19,719
Nan, I said wait!

359
00:43:20,119 --> 00:43:22,719
I said wait! Didn't you hear me?

360
00:43:23,119 --> 00:43:24,440
Open the door!

361
00:43:24,519 --> 00:43:25,920
-Thee.
-Nan!

362
00:43:26,000 --> 00:43:29,360
-Thee, calm down.
-Open the door. Come out and talk!

363
00:43:30,280 --> 00:43:31,719
What's going on, Mom?

364
00:43:31,800 --> 00:43:33,760
It's nothing. Go back to bed.

365
00:43:51,679 --> 00:43:52,760
What did you do last night?

366
00:44:02,760 --> 00:44:04,119
I saw a ghost last night.

367
00:44:06,559 --> 00:44:08,159
What did you do last night? Answer me!

368
00:44:10,960 --> 00:44:14,599
I'm serious. I went to that haunted house
with my friends last night.

369
00:44:14,679 --> 00:44:16,840
And there's a dark shadow that floated by
and we all screamed.

370
00:44:16,920 --> 00:44:19,920
If you can't come up with a better story,
get out of my face!

371
00:44:41,199 --> 00:44:43,800
It's nothing, son. Eat your food.

372
00:45:01,119 --> 00:45:03,960
Not now, Mom. I have a splitting headache.

373
00:45:04,039 --> 00:45:06,199
My granddaughter saw a ghost
and no one cares.

374
00:45:06,400 --> 00:45:08,400
Mom, Nan was lying.

375
00:45:08,719 --> 00:45:11,400
She went out with her friends
and told us she was working on a report.

376
00:45:11,480 --> 00:45:14,599
Even if she went out,
it doesn't mean she lied about that.

377
00:45:15,400 --> 00:45:19,440
Seriously, do you agree with your husband
that she lied about seeing a ghost?

378
00:45:19,800 --> 00:45:22,639
Are you going to blame everything on Thee?

379
00:45:22,880 --> 00:45:27,119
If he wants to be the head of the family
then he has to take the responsibility.

380
00:45:28,239 --> 00:45:30,400
If you didn't get knocked up,

381
00:45:30,880 --> 00:45:33,320
I would've never let you marry him.

382
00:45:33,960 --> 00:45:34,840
Mom.

383
00:45:35,320 --> 00:45:37,000
And if your dad were still alive...

384
00:45:37,480 --> 00:45:39,760
Mom, stop comparing Thee to Dad, okay?

385
00:45:41,039 --> 00:45:42,960
Dad had passed away for many years now.

386
00:45:43,760 --> 00:45:46,320
And even if Dad was still here,

387
00:45:46,559 --> 00:45:48,559
no matter how much Dad hated Thee,

388
00:45:48,639 --> 00:45:50,679
Dad wouldn't have made Nan
hate her own father!

389
00:45:52,360 --> 00:45:55,519
You're willing to put your kids at risk.
You're so selfish.

390
00:46:12,760 --> 00:46:15,679
Hey, how is your new home?
Everyone is happy, right?

391
00:46:16,960 --> 00:46:17,920
It's fine.

392
00:46:18,719 --> 00:46:22,320
Okay, another thing.
Our salary will come late for this month.

393
00:46:24,599 --> 00:46:27,320
What? Don't act like you're shocked.
Come on.

394
00:46:27,400 --> 00:46:29,679
It is all our fault.

395
00:46:29,760 --> 00:46:32,800
We didn't reach the sales target
that our Bangkok branch expected.

396
00:46:32,880 --> 00:46:36,679
It's just a little problem.
It's not a big deal, right?

397
00:46:37,559 --> 00:46:38,400
And?

398
00:46:38,480 --> 00:46:40,760
This had happened to me before.

399
00:46:40,840 --> 00:46:43,199
It was for three months at that time.
I was so stressed at first.

400
00:46:43,280 --> 00:46:45,480
I thought, how could there be
no salary for three months?

401
00:46:45,559 --> 00:46:47,400
But then, I got paid in a lump sum.

402
00:46:47,480 --> 00:46:49,599
And there's the compensation, too.

403
00:46:49,960 --> 00:46:52,400
Now, when the company says
they will pay late,

404
00:46:52,480 --> 00:46:55,000
I'm actually very happy.
Don't be stressed.

405
00:46:55,280 --> 00:46:59,079
Every cloud has a silver lining.
Don't worry. It's not a big deal.

