00:47:07,519 --> 00:47:09,800
PREVIOUS BALANCE 1,316.10 BAHT

409
00:47:09,880 --> 00:47:12,679
Let's cancel Nan's
Blackberry calling package.

410
00:47:13,119 --> 00:47:15,800
It's too much for a ninth-grade student
to have a thousand-baht phone bill.

411
00:47:16,039 --> 00:47:19,000
I already told you so, but you insisted.

412
00:47:22,000 --> 00:47:23,840
Is Nan asleep yet? I will go talk to her.

413
00:47:24,119 --> 00:47:27,840
She went to her friend's dorm for a report
and she will be home late.

414
00:47:28,360 --> 00:47:29,239
What?

415
00:47:29,679 --> 00:47:33,159
She still dares to come home late?
I thought I made myself clear last time.

416
00:47:34,400 --> 00:47:38,079
Nan is very stubborn. She resists harder
when you are harder on her.

417
00:47:39,320 --> 00:47:41,920
Your mother makes even the nicest kid
become a spoiled brat.

418
00:47:42,519 --> 00:47:44,159
It's fortunate that
she didn't raise Nat too.

419
00:48:04,039 --> 00:48:06,440
Sorry. I was being too harsh on you.

420
00:48:14,079 --> 00:48:15,679
So which friend
did she spend the night with?

421
00:48:16,360 --> 00:48:18,800
Hey, what did you guys see
the other night?

422
00:48:24,000 --> 00:48:26,119
I didn't see anything myself.

423
00:48:27,119 --> 00:48:28,719
But when I heard Mai scream,

424
00:48:29,159 --> 00:48:30,320
I ran.

425
00:48:30,440 --> 00:48:31,480
What a jerk!

426
00:48:34,800 --> 00:48:36,679
Maybe Mai had fooled us?

427
00:48:36,840 --> 00:48:38,400
I don't think so.

428
00:48:38,960 --> 00:48:41,079
When she screamed,

429
00:48:41,320 --> 00:48:43,079
she looked horrified.

430
00:48:50,079 --> 00:48:51,039
Jerk!

431
00:48:58,079 --> 00:48:59,559
Nan!

432
00:49:04,199 --> 00:49:05,480
This is "working on a report"?

433
00:49:05,960 --> 00:49:07,519
How dare you behave like this?

434
00:49:07,800 --> 00:49:09,760
Like what?
I was just playing with my friend.

435
00:49:10,119 --> 00:49:12,559
Do you know how embarrassing
that was for me?

436
00:49:13,000 --> 00:49:13,920
Embarrassed?

437
00:49:14,719 --> 00:49:16,679
Aren't you embarrassed
to touch a guy like that?

438
00:49:17,559 --> 00:49:18,840
Didn't your grandma teach you that?

439
00:49:19,079 --> 00:49:22,079
She always does. You never did.

440
00:49:23,960 --> 00:49:27,119
Don't think of having kids
if you can't raise them.

441
00:49:28,079 --> 00:49:29,960
I still haven't excused you
for lying to me last time!

442
00:49:30,559 --> 00:49:32,360
And you dare to talk to me like this?

443
00:49:32,599 --> 00:49:34,519
Have you ever listened
when I talked politely?

444
00:49:34,599 --> 00:49:36,599
I already told you I saw a ghost.

445
00:49:36,880 --> 00:49:38,840
Yet you called me a liar
instead of being worried for me.

446
00:49:38,920 --> 00:49:40,599
-That's because you lied!
-No, I didn't!

447
00:49:40,920 --> 00:49:43,679
-Your village is haunted!
-Stop that nonsense already!

448
00:49:43,760 --> 00:49:46,599
It's not nonsense.
Your village is haunted!

449
00:49:46,679 --> 00:49:48,079
The whole village knows the truth!

450
00:49:48,159 --> 00:49:49,159
-You are the--
-Stop talking!

451
00:49:49,239 --> 00:49:50,719
You are the only one in denial!

452
00:49:50,800 --> 00:49:52,280
Your village is haunted! There are ghosts!

453
00:49:52,360 --> 00:49:54,360
Stop it! I said there are no ghosts! None!

454
00:49:54,440 --> 00:49:55,760
-There are!
-No there aren't!

455
00:49:55,840 --> 00:49:57,840
There are! Your village has ghosts!

456
00:49:57,920 --> 00:50:00,360
There are ghosts here!

457
00:50:15,480 --> 00:50:16,400
What are you doing?

458
00:50:23,920 --> 00:50:25,079
-Get out!
-Let me go!

459
00:50:25,239 --> 00:50:26,920
-I said get out of the car!
-What are you doing?

460
00:50:27,000 --> 00:50:28,159
-No! I'm not going!
-Get down!

461
00:50:28,239 --> 00:50:30,920
Let me go!

462
00:50:31,159 --> 00:50:32,199
Let me go!

463
00:50:32,280 --> 00:50:33,239
-Come here.
-Let me go!

464
00:50:33,320 --> 00:50:34,199
-Come here.
-Let me go!

465
00:50:34,280 --> 00:50:36,000
-I told you to come here.
-Let me go!

466
00:50:36,079 --> 00:50:37,079
Come in!

467
00:50:37,840 --> 00:50:40,199
Let me go, Dad! I don't want to go in!

468
00:50:40,280 --> 00:50:42,599
I said let me go already!

469
00:50:42,960 --> 00:50:44,920
No! I don't want to go in!

470
00:50:45,000 --> 00:50:46,199
Come in!

471
00:50:46,280 --> 00:50:47,440
Let go of me!

472
00:50:47,599 --> 00:50:48,719
-Come in!
-Let go of me!

473
00:50:48,800 --> 00:50:49,840
Let go of me!

474
00:50:49,920 --> 00:50:50,960
-See?
-Let go of me!

475
00:50:51,039 --> 00:50:52,840
-Look, are there any ghosts?
-I won't look!

476
00:50:52,920 --> 00:50:54,840
Let me go!

477
00:50:55,320 --> 00:50:56,239
Let me go!

478
00:50:56,320 --> 00:50:57,280
Let me go!

479
00:50:57,360 --> 00:50:58,400
Let me go already!

480
00:50:58,480 --> 00:50:59,400
Let me go!

481
00:50:59,480 --> 00:51:00,719
Let me go!

482
00:53:34,239 --> 00:53:35,239
Bye, Mom.

483
00:53:38,480 --> 00:53:39,440
Nan.

484
00:53:40,280 --> 00:53:41,599
Nan is going to stay with her friend.

485
00:53:42,039 --> 00:53:43,360
She will be back on the weekend.

486
00:53:43,440 --> 00:53:44,679
Why did you let her go?

487
00:53:47,760 --> 00:53:51,280
My mom will take her back to Bangkok
if I don't let her go.

488
00:53:52,000 --> 00:53:52,960
Do you want that?

489
00:54:28,800 --> 00:54:29,719
Where are you?

490
00:54:30,119 --> 00:54:32,199
I am at the airport now.

491
00:54:32,320 --> 00:54:34,719
I am about to board my plane to Bangkok.

492
00:54:35,519 --> 00:54:38,440
I got called back
to take care of the marketing there.

493
00:54:38,880 --> 00:54:40,400
What about me, Yoi?

494
00:54:41,840 --> 00:54:42,840
Thee.

495
00:54:43,360 --> 00:54:44,679
We are all adults here.

496
00:54:45,039 --> 00:54:47,719
Don't you get what I mean?

497
00:54:47,960 --> 00:54:48,800
Yoi.

498
00:54:49,199 --> 00:54:50,039
Yoi!

499
00:54:51,760 --> 00:54:53,000
You bastard.

500
00:54:53,960 --> 00:54:55,679
It's good that the company is stable now.

501
00:54:55,760 --> 00:54:58,079
We got to this point because of your help.

502
00:54:59,440 --> 00:55:01,760
I was so surprised when I saw you.

503
00:55:01,960 --> 00:55:04,119
I didn't think you know where I live,
Mr. Manop.

504
00:55:04,440 --> 00:55:07,519
It's good that you came here early
or I would have gone out by now.

505
00:55:15,960 --> 00:55:17,639
How come you have never called me?

506
00:55:19,239 --> 00:55:22,519
I know you are very busy.
I was afraid to bother you.

507
00:55:25,480 --> 00:55:28,360
My life is so hectic
because I don't have you nowadays.

508
00:55:30,320 --> 00:55:32,480
I heard that
your new secretary is very good.

509
00:55:34,239 --> 00:55:36,039
But I liked it better
when you were working for me.

510
00:55:38,880 --> 00:55:42,679
I will be very happy
if we can work together again.

511
00:56:06,079 --> 00:56:07,039
Hey!

512
00:56:08,639 --> 00:56:09,639
Thee.

513
00:56:19,920 --> 00:56:21,239
Why are you home early today?

514
00:56:23,360 --> 00:56:24,400
I have a headache.

515
00:56:25,320 --> 00:56:26,440
So I left early.

516
00:57:08,360 --> 00:57:10,119
Thee, I'm going to pick Nat up.

517
00:57:29,599 --> 00:57:30,480
Parn.

518
00:57:32,840 --> 00:57:33,719
Parn.

519
00:57:41,639 --> 00:57:42,760
Thee.

520
00:57:43,480 --> 00:57:44,840
What's the matter?

521
00:57:47,639 --> 00:57:48,599
Nothing.

522
00:57:49,760 --> 00:57:50,800
I just have a headache.

